<taxonomicName authority="Casal" authorityName="Casal" box="[151,446,477,504]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Limaytilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="587" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huarpe">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,446,477,504]" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,368,477,504]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">Limaytilla huarpe</emphasis>
Casal
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,519,477,539]" box="[151,519,512,539]" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">(Figs 3, 4, 15, 17, 19, 21, 25–27)</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="587" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,584,1187]" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,584,611]" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male. Specimens large and robust (12.0– 
<quantity box="[758,861,584,611]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5699999999999998" pageId="4" pageNumber="587" unit="mm" value="15.7">15.7 mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[981,1119,585,611]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.05" metricValueMax="3.7" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="4" pageNumber="587" unit="mm" value="3.05" valueMax="3.7" valueMin="2.4">2.4–3.7 mm</quantity>
wide) (11.0– 
<quantity box="[1275,1377,584,611]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" pageId="4" pageNumber="587" unit="mm" value="17.5">17.5 mm</quantity>
long 
<emphasis box="[151,213,622,647]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Cambra, R. A. &amp; Quintero, A. D. &amp; Pagliano, G." box="[222,452,621,648]" pageId="4" pageNumber="587" pagination="37 - 70" refId="ref6757" refString="Cambra, R. A., Quintero, A. D. &amp; Pagliano, G. (2016) Revision of Limaytilla Casal, 1964 (Hymenoptera: Mutillidae: Sphaeropthalmini), including the first apterous male in the genus. Il Naturalista Valtellinese, Atti Museo civ. Storia natural Morbegno, 27, 37 - 70." type="journal article" year="2016">
Cambra 
<emphasis box="[320,372,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">et al</emphasis>
., 2016
</bibRefCitation>
) (Figs 3, 4); head quadrangular with rounded contours in dorsal view (Fig. 19); basal ventral tooth simple (Fig. 17, indicated); antennal tubercle projected as a slight sub-triangular lamellate protuberance (flattened laterally) on inner face (Fig. 19, indicated); first segment of metasoma relatively short (1.4x as long as wide) (
<figureCitation box="[264,350,729,755]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–29" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1902,1927]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,217,1852]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,217,1852]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 20–29. Limaytilla spp. ♂. 20, L. diaguita sp. nov., first metasomal segment (dorsal). 21, L. huarpe, first metasomal segment (dorsal). 22–24, L. diaguita: 22, genitalia; 23, paramere (apical); 24, gonobase (side). 25–27, L. huarpe: 25, genitalia; 26, paramere (apical); 27, gonobase (side). 28, 29, L. orlandoi: 28, habitus (lateral); 29, habitus (dorsal)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3227932/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
); gonobase densely hairy on sides (
<figureCitation box="[759,845,729,755]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–29" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1902,1927]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,217,1852]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,217,1852]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 20–29. Limaytilla spp. ♂. 20, L. diaguita sp. nov., first metasomal segment (dorsal). 21, L. huarpe, first metasomal segment (dorsal). 22–24, L. diaguita: 22, genitalia; 23, paramere (apical); 24, gonobase (side). 25–27, L. huarpe: 25, genitalia; 26, paramere (apical); 27, gonobase (side). 28, 29, L. orlandoi: 28, habitus (lateral); 29, habitus (dorsal)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3227932/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
); distal third of paramere with numerous long setae (
<figureCitation box="[159,289,764,792]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–29" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1902,1927]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,217,1852]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,217,1852]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 20–29. Limaytilla spp. ♂. 20, L. diaguita sp. nov., first metasomal segment (dorsal). 21, L. huarpe, first metasomal segment (dorsal). 22–24, L. diaguita: 22, genitalia; 23, paramere (apical); 24, gonobase (side). 25–27, L. huarpe: 25, genitalia; 26, paramere (apical); 27, gonobase (side). 28, 29, L. orlandoi: 28, habitus (lateral); 29, habitus (dorsal)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3227932/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">Figs 25, 26</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="587" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,584,1187]" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,800,827]" pageId="4" pageNumber="587">Description.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Casal, O. H." box="[353,498,801,828]" pageId="4" pageNumber="587" pagination="81 - 103" refId="ref6819" refString="Casal, O. H. (1964) Revision de Lymaitilla. Nuevo genero endemico y nocturno de Sphaeropthalmini (Hymenoptera, Mutillidae). Acta Zoologica Lilloana, 20, 81 - 103." type="journal article" year="1964">Casal (1964)</bibRefCitation>
described and illustrated this species in detail; we only add images of habitus and characters useful for its identification.
</paragraph>
